WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.560
Hello, my name is Allyson Rose, and I am a senior in college double majoring in biochemistry

00:06.560 --> 00:08.400
and neuroscience.

00:08.400 --> 00:13.880
I participated in two regional and two international space settlement design competitions, and

00:13.880 --> 00:18.400
I can honestly say that the experiences changed my life.

00:18.400 --> 00:24.520
Coming from a small town in a landlocked state, I had very little exposure to diverse interactions

00:24.520 --> 00:27.980
prior to my participation in the competitions.

00:27.980 --> 00:32.660
By meeting and working directly with people from all across the world on our shared goal

00:32.660 --> 00:37.880
of developing a strong project, I gained a long-standing desire to learn from people

00:37.880 --> 00:41.740
that come from backgrounds dissimilar to my own.

00:41.740 --> 00:46.520
By assuming a leadership role as president of my company one year, I also learned that

00:46.520 --> 00:52.100
having people with these vastly different experiences come together to address roadblocks,

00:52.100 --> 00:56.380
it can result in the most innovative solutions.

00:56.380 --> 01:00.800
I would highly recommend competing in the design competitions because they offer an

01:00.800 --> 01:04.660
opportunity for growth no matter what your current interests are.

01:04.660 --> 01:10.260
Personally, I will be attending medical school next year, but I chose to highlight one story

01:10.260 --> 01:16.020
from my involvement in the design competitions during the recent application phase because

01:16.020 --> 01:20.980
that moment had such a long-lasting impact on who I am as a person to this very day.

